{{Lowercase title}}
{{rough translation}}
{{refimprove|time=2019-08-20T03:16:21+00:00}}
“'''de jure'''”（{{Lang-la|dē iūre}}， "by law"（法律上），{{IPA-la|deː ˈjuːrɛ|pron}}、{{IPA-en|deɪ ˈdʒʊəri, di -}} {{respell|day|_|JOOR|ee|,_|dee|_-}}），是来自[[拉丁語|拉丁語]]的法律用语，與“[[de_facto|de facto]]”（直译作“事实上”）相對。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.Dictionary.com/browse/de-jure |title=de jure |publisher=dictionary.com |accessdate=2016-07-11 |archivedate=2020-08-13 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200813010406/https://www.dictionary.com/browse/de-jure |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在英语中，它表示“法律上規定的情況”，尤其是雖有規定但實際上並非如此的情況。雖然De Jure是法律用語，但是有時候也會在法律以外的語境下使用。<ref>{{cite web |title=Definition of De Jure by Merriam-Webster: Did you know? |url=https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/de%20jure |website=Merriam-Webster |accessdate=2019-11-22 |archive-date=2020-02-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200211004606/https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/de%20jure |dead-url=no }}</ref>此詞使用時絕大多數時候都會與de facto並列，以突出理想與現實的差別。此詞語通常以形容詞方式使用、以斜體字書寫。<ref>{{cite web |title=Legal English: “De Facto/De Jure” |url=https://onlinelaw.wustl.edu/blog/legal-english-de-factode-jure/ |publisher=Law Degrees Available Online |accessdate=2019-11-22 |date=2012-12-28 |archivedate=2020-02-11 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200211004609/https://onlinelaw.wustl.edu/blog/legal-english-de-factode-jure/ |dead-url=no |language=en }}</ref>在商業上，De Jure也會用來形容滿足所有法律要求、已經正式成立的[[有限責任公司|有限責任公司]]。在某些[[司法管轄區|司法管轄區]]，即使沒有滿足成立公司相關的要求，實務上存在的公司也可能獲得責任限制的保護（de facto protection）。<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kenton |first=Will |title=How De Jure Corporations Work |url=https://www.investopedia.com/terms/d/de-jure-corporation.asp |accessdate=2019-11-22 |publisher=Investopedia |archivedate=2019-12-07 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207191546/https://www.investopedia.com/terms/d/de-jure-corporation.asp |dead-url=no |language=en }}</ref>

